The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 LOOSE CHANGE

 ING Vysya Life Insurance Company has declared an annual bonus between 2 per cent and 8.21 per cent across all its participating plans. The bonus rates declared are based on the company?s investment performance during the last fiscal. The highest bonus announced is 8.21 per cent for the Best Years? Retirement Plan and the minimum bonus announced is 2 per cent for endowment plan Reassuring Life. The company has given a 5 per cent bonus for its money-back plan, Maximising Life. The company has 16 life insurance plans, including three unit-linked products. 

 IDBI has increased the interest rates on its Suvidha fixed deposits by 25-50 basis points. A 10-year fixed deposit of up to Rs 15 lakh will now fetch the maximum rate of 7.5 per cent. Senior citizens will get a higher interest rate of 8.5 per cent. Deposits of one year to one-and-a-half years? maturity will earn 7 per cent interest against 6.5 per cent earlier. 

 Franklin Templeton Investments (India) has announced a tax-free dividend of 60 per cent for its equity-oriented Prima Fund. Pursuant to payment of the dividend the net asset value of the units will come down by Rs 6. All investors registered in the dividend plan as on July 19 will receive this dividend. 




